parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to a significant risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbag may not deploy properly or may rupture, causing metal fragments to strike the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: No symptoms reported
as the issue is related to the recall repair delay.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy
airbag light illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of communication and poor service from dealers can lead to frustration and a sense of neglect among vehicle owners.
symptoms: No return call from the dealer to schedule an appointment
dealer's excuse for not having parts
lack of communication from the dealer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle stalls
or the transmission makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4WD system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle engages 4WD mode without warning
the vehicle loses traction
the vehicle's handling is affected
or the 4WD system makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
or the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine surges
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
or the vehicle's transmission slips or jerks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the multifunction switch can cause the turn signals, windshield wipers, and high beams to malfunction or become inoperable, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete failure of turn signals
windshield wipers
and high beams; turn signals flashing in the wrong direction; windshield wipers stopping unexpectedly; high beams not functioning.
